<title>ITALY: Italy to abolish tax on CDs for non-residents.</title>
<headline>Italy to abolish tax on CDs for non-residents.</headline>
<dateline>MILAN 1996-08-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Non-resident holders of Italian certificates of deposit will no longer be subject to a withholding tax from January 1 1997, Milan financial daily Il Sole 24 Ore reported on Tuesday.</p>
<p>Following a recent shake-up of taxes on investment income, certificates of deposit held by Italian residents are now taxed at a rate of 27 percent.</p>
<p>Italy announced earlier this year that the withholding tax for non-residents would be abolished from the beginning of next year on Italian government bonds, including treasury bills (BOTs), certificates (CCTs) and BTPs.</p>
<p>Swiss inveastors will not be eligible for the tax exemption for legal reasons.</p>
<p>-- Milan newsroom +392-66102321</p>
